igating swagger compatibility**\n\nI need to figure out if swagger annotation version 2.2.25 works with 5.0.0. I think I should look at the POM parent for dependency management to see the version it uses. Maybe I should inspect the parent POM file to find the version details. I'll consider searching through the cached parent to check for any relevant information that could help clarify this compatibility issue. Let's see what it reveals!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00459a980397370a016a404f5b3ac08195bc51b57f754db36a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQE9qUch0gpkPlP2qSWzW4EG1xsd3hHUTl5jdYHU_WXNKsq08wB43xKFTgz8fceuz78HfStNOuMswbDCFaxn5hviquOscZ1nXYYzWKBDkFPGoKqZ60ypH_v5KyF2YAfqDnFoxpm2qlSNh6q8pGt6SrLj-Yiy0frsdPSiL-aj7o7AQhXr3Xjl34OyPaQKr_1WBMXsk23meWyKTuYrUVewvF5P-Pq4Edsq9VGa3efhq_Rqj0xvyinO4RP4Uys-TSEebjlw5NlLjSdhIuCp44eV6vt5oY8MMR6CMkUUjqETp7dDpbVplN6r6136vZI-hKdMafet6fJI_khZDpHgcDgXlVEqlL0dgKdRAGXk15fMWafCob3iTzJrfybr39yjEPVvx8pVqsYYs1h9UGo76IgBAlFVB2Axsbjhv07iQtsHdYbH9KFkuoUCijZ5Aqo8XxIh6xjoB35lRk3Ed6IsizysS4-GdXyjNcXVMo9fNghC92FtpCrY2OWCC0Cu9VRw-aqCsgQ6uBEgZhDxar5QTYa3eUwrH0zhWBaFk5FDcCSNlDhF9J91-Y-9V-Lz58HWJIHDLfCNTphiQ4LmfNY6YprDVmo0xGYWsyKO-vTIaoOzekfAE1LMydKw0yrGlTKEgCPjynisbBrELXRDhmp_5SH3SHqTD8RaQVotoJXebiNsdbEhE39dnP1yPjLLqDwTfWSqsNPp4BI7QuO6OqgB2DWcDlHblgShpJvbCSejPz6ARgrvoOMDtKfNwpa3jlbiy_1zMlUtHLMHRTkfnn4_1JVKYPSJrxFMf5ySI0TjWxNCREQYUwbvyuimKxZpTkerJCYjS2t8jYfeIDrazU3rLi6MNHHeXowNMpM67mAcXI8qXFy4tUpvnzW8bw083Ka5rAYCH2l1EJDKGO7RvET8EEb7PUHPdj4DH1d8AXse-ExHgjOeC0R5Jiwti0-NbScZu4ehwZuEN-A70tL-La752zLJMXZPhi-ulEggxlPfik9w2OnwHoAgsREwiPbOs1h2iT3vRQm3BLAWupaX3ww2Rw6Y-OQ3VREY3acrVitkLyYbfZqmwOAbZCgw8IJmJ1YSTiv_HTtj0IRnyx_GFwJCQfGUsOYg9tZASjsJHsUGCW48BRmC_JUDQlzOIr3g2U25cBeZd87M6zYFNqwwXFk7d8jwp82pRPev5n-lN_C7zhnOeo36dN3ysOs4GlRur9vRMsdR3m2u2SDsXgUGBdQah4sofarOpXVa4zizLE6M_LseXbIbfeIXwggPsxh_zIe40rNRSb-9cYB6SYNTl0QFoROrtk8uvmTx95cJj3p2lmrT3t9eBZgc_oofpD1ATjJcZI_sOOqYBNcZLdFIfrT3T5zzqE7y6HCpEXfjkeC0VokNmuxx0kN-NCQ_GIs