ncies**\\n\\nI’m thinking about possible duplicates since the library module POM has both generator and swagger provided. This means their APIs are accessible in the module's public and protected signatures. The user might be only calling `new Swagger2Module()` in tests, which requires the generator type for compilation, but the annotation classes don’t need to be visible unless referenced in tests. I need to consider the risks associated with existing tests hard-coding Jackson 2 imports while adapting to version 5 with Jackson 3. It’s best to stick with swagger 2.2.41 to ensure compatibility.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The artifact is a VicTools module, not the standalone generator. Its POM marks both the core jsonschema-generator and Swagger 2 annotations as provided, while the documented meaningful use is to register Swagger2Module with SchemaGenerator and annotate model classes with io.swagger.v3 annotations.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"com.github.victools:jsonschema-generator:5.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"jsonschema-module-swagger-2 is applied through SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder/SchemaGenerator, but the module POM declares jsonschema-generator with provided scope.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"io.swagger.core.v3:swagger-annotations:2.2.41\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The module derives schema attributes from @Schema and @ArraySchema, but swagger-annotations is declared with provided scope; 2.2.41 is the version managed by the 5.0.0 parent POM.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For version 5.0.0, use Jackson 3 package names in test code. Import tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode or tools.jackson.databind.node.ObjectNode instead of com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode; the upstream 5.0.0 docs and bytecode show SchemaGenerator.generateSchema() returning Jackson 3 ObjectNode/JsonNode types.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Existing 4.38.0 tests import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode; carrying that import forward causes the javac failure shown in the issue.\",\n    \"Using an older Swagger annotations dependency may compile for simple annotations but can drift from the version the 5.0.0 module was compiled and tested against.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_00459a980397370a016a404f76db8c8195860f58d1658e885f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1337, "output": 909, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31430, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782599534650, "responseId": "resp_00459a980397370a016a404f6f1e648195a4f69441f52b6310"}, "toolResults": []}
